
WAF VIP aur WAF SNAT â€“ Complete Explanation (Simple Hindi)

1) WAF (Web Application Firewall) kya hai?
WAF ek security layer hota hai jo web application ko attacks, unauthorized access aur malicious traffic se protect karta hai.

2) WAF VIP kya hota hai?
VIP ka matlab Virtual IP hota hai.
WAF VIP wo IP hota hai jahan se application duniya ko dikhayi deti hai.
Saari incoming traffic (user, application, CBS, etc.) sabse pehle isi IP par aati hai.

Example:
User / Application -> WAF VIP -> WAF -> Backend Server

Isliye VIP usually ek hi hota hai, taaki entry point simple aur fixed rahe.

3) WAF SNAT kya hota hai?
SNAT ka matlab Source Network Address Translation hota hai.
Jab WAF backend server ko request bhejta hai, to wo apna source IP change karke ek SNAT IP dikhata hai.
Backend server ko user ka real IP nahi, balki WAF ka SNAT IP dikhai deta hai.

4) WAF VIP ek aur WAF SNAT multiple kyun hote hain?
WAF VIP:
- Single entry gate hota hai
- Client-facing IP hota hai
- DNS aur integration ke liye easy hota hai

WAF SNAT (multiple IP):
- High traffic handle karne ke liye
- Port exhaustion se bachne ke liye
- Load distribution ke liye
- High availability ke liye
- Backend firewall me easy whitelisting ke liye

Isliye SNAT hamesha ek pool me multiple IPs ke saath configure hota hai.

5) Traffic Flow (Simple):
User
  |
  v
WAF VIP (1 IP)
  |
  v
WAF Engine
  |
  v
SNAT IP Pool (multiple IPs)
  |
  v
Backend Servers

Backend server ko hamesha SNAT IP hi dikhai deta hai.

6) Real Life Example:
VIP = Bank ka main counter
SNAT = Counter ke staff ka ID

Customer counter par aata hai (VIP),
lekin andar ka cashier sirf staff ID (SNAT) dekhta hai.

7) One-line Summary:
WAF VIP client-facing single IP hota hai, jabki WAF SNAT multiple IPs ka pool hota hai jo backend communication ko secure, stable aur scalable banata hai.